other_tests.findings: Retrocecal appendix measuring approximately 9 mm in diameter at its tip with associated periappendiceal inflammatory stranding. The appendix demonstrates restricted diffusion. Visualized hepatic parenchyma, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary dilatation or gallstones. Remainder of small and large bowel loops in the abdomen are unremarkable.
